==Demographics==
As of the 2020 census, there were 340 people, 184 housing units, and 132 families in Rosburg. Rosburg had 298 [[White Americans|White]] people, 3 [[African Americans]], 5 [[Native Americans in the United States|Native Americans]], 6 [[Asian Americans|Asians]], 8 people who were from some other race, and 20 people from two or more races. 14 people were [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |title=Explore Census Data |url=https://data.census.gov/profile/Rosburg_CDP,_Washington?g=160XX00US5359845 |access-date=2023-05-17 |website=data.census.gov}}</ref>

The ancestry of Rosburg was 15.5% [[English Americans|English]], 14.2% [[Italian Americans|Italian]], 13.1% [[German Americans|German]], 10% [[Irish Americans|Irish]], 6.6% [[African diaspora|Sub-Saharan African]], 1.6% [[French Americans|French]], 1.3% [[Scottish Americans|Scottish]], and 0.8% [[Norwegian Americans|Norwegian.]]<ref name=":0" />

The median age in Rosburg was 34.8 years old. 15% of the population were older than 65, with 12.3% 65 to 74, 2.6% 75 to 84, and 0.0% older than 85.<ref name=":0" />

The median income was $87,500 in Rosburg. 7.9% of the population were in poverty, with 7.4% of people 18 to 64 years being in poverty, and 29.8% of people 65 or older being in poverty.<ref name=":0" />

